alert.note: Alert for Eastern Alachua; Western Putnam (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Jacksonville (Northeast Florida and Southeast Georgia)
info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 6:53PM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Alachua and northwestern Putnam Counties through 745 PM EDT... At 653 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along a line extending from near Hawthorne to Rochelle. Movement was east at 35 mph. HAZARD...Winds around 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Interlachen, Hawthorne, Melrose Landing, Bardin, Hollister, Florahome, Rochelle, Johnson, Carraway and Mannville. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
